Patch Set 17:

> Patch Set 17: Code-Review-1
> 
> It could be made a bit more generic by using -EOPNOTSUPP as the error return, and then handle cases where any OSD doesn't handle the ZERO_RANGE at all.
> 

Yes we could use -EOPNOTSUPP here, it's only that I could not figure out from the MDT layer how to tell if proceeding with zeroing is the approapriate action:
- -EOPNOTSUPP return from osd-zfs? no zeroing;
- -EOPNOTSUPP return from osd-ldiskfs with 'od_fallocate_zero_blocks==-1'? no zeroing;
- -EOPNOTSUPP return from osd-ldiskfs otherwise, continue with zeroing;

...
